.TH "lpfc_selective_reset" 9 "lpfc_selective_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_selective_reset \- Offline then onlines the port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_selective_reset
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
lpfc_hba pointer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the port is configured to allow a reset then the hba is brought
offline then online.
.SH "NOTES"
Assumes any error from \fBlpfc_do_offline\fP will be negative.
Do not make this function static.
.SH "RETURN"
\fBlpfc_do_offline\fP return code if not zero
-EIO reset not configured or error posting the event
zero for success
